criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult patients 18-85 years old

          -  patients scheduled to undergo foot surgery

        Exclusion Criteria

          -  patients with neuropathy caused by genetic, metabolic and inflammatory diseases, as
             well as toxic agents and drugs (eg chemotherapy agents);

          -  patients with chronic pain syndrome;

          -  patients with contraindications for regional anesthesia (e.g., allergy to local
             anesthetics);

          -  chronic consumption of opioids.
